      "evidence": [
        "WiFi API functions repeatedly do `resolve runtime` then one method call (`ListWifiSSIDs`, `ConnectToWifi`, `DisconnectWifi`, `ToggleDevice`, `applyCaptiveRules`) with minimal added behavior.",
        "Event API has paired wrappers (`Publish*` and `*Transitions`) that mostly resolve broker/default context and forward to broker methods.",
        "C2C entrypoints (`C2CMode`, `UnaliveC2C`, `C2CConnect`) always allocate a new flow and immediately forward to a single method."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Collapse pass-through layers by exposing a cohesive service object (or package-level minimal API) per domain with explicit lifecycle; keep only wrappers that enforce policy, translation, or compatibility and remove redundant aliases.",
