        "Config update registry centralizes many field-level patch adapters on the broad `SysConfig`, reinforcing a single shared mutable bag instead of narrower bounded contexts."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Introduce bounded config ports per domain (connectivity/runtime/startram/penpai and per-urbit subdomains) and move callsites to domain-specific mutation APIs; keep compatibility mapping at boundaries only, then retire duplicated subconfig adapter functions.",
